![](Images/AРМІЯINFORM/2023-04-07T41-00-00-04-00/19c7174c-1da2-435f-a2aa-7f83c280f220.jpg)First Deputy Minister of Defense of Ukraine Lieutenant General Oleksandr Pavlyukvpw interagency meeting on the possibilities of production in Ukraine of modern equipment and equipment for mine

Ukraine is the most replaced country in the world. The area of contaminated with excellent objects of territories reaches 180 thousand square kilometers.

Demand groups work to solve the problem, but are not able to speed up with an extremely large amount of work.

Read also:

[The problem of mine safety will be relevant for Ukraine for tens of year](https://armyinform.com.ua/2023/04/04/problema-protyminnoyi-bezpeky-bude-aktualnoyu-dlya-ukrayiny-protyagom-desyatkiv-rokiv/)In order to resolve this issue on April 6, 2023, on the initiative of the First Department of Defense of Ukraine, Lieutenant General Alexander Pavlyukivka was an interagency meeting "Possibilities of production in Ukraine of modern equipment and technique for mine".

In addition to representatives delegated by ministries and profile departments, representatives of state and private enterprises were invited in the meeting.

According to Lieutenant General Oleksandr Pavlyuk, the Ministry of Defense, the Armed Forces and other other ways are already taking some steps to create new units, as well as the preparation and better equipment of those that already exist.

- The demining process should not be delayed for hundreds and even decades. In the shortest possible time, it is necessary to do everything possible to establish a safe, peaceful life and work of people in the liberated territories, - said Alexanderpavlyuk.

The main task of this meeting was to study the possibilities of domestic producers, their ability to provide special units with means of differentiation and technology.

- Need individual sets of protection of sappers, the necessary equipment for the worms, equipment for transportation of personnel, robotic platforms, trails to mine the terrain, - said Alexander Pavlyuk.

During the meeting, representatives of the Armed Forces support forces, DSST, other consignments voiced the specific needs for modern technical means, necessary for the fulfillment of the tasks of the demining units, and the basic requirements for them.

[!(Images/AРМІЯINFORM/2023-04-07T41-00-00-04-00/882b0f79-08a5-4b28-ba9c-483516c76172-1-150x150.jpg)](https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/882b0f79-08a5-4b28-ba9c-483516c76172-1.jpg)

In particular, the head of the administration of the State Special Service of Defense of Ukraine Major General Bogdan Bondar reported that the units especially need manual demining means, machines for mechanized miners, means of monitoring of territories, including drones.

The Commander of the Armed Forces of the Armed Forces Brigadny General Dmitry Gerega, in his turn, reported that the units of support use during demining wedged machines of various modifications: Slovak machines Bozena and their counterparts, but in the near future the need for such technique will only grow.

In the further discussion of the capabilities of Ukrainian producers, representatives of other ministries, departments, companies and organizations took part in the demining rate.

The First Deputy Minister for Strategic and Industry, Oleg, suggested to create powerful cooperative hubs at the public and private sector bases, where enterprises will be involved in cutting types of work.

The idea was supported by the CEO of Ukroboronprom, Yuriy Gusev, which reported that a state-owned enterprise already has a number of developments, in particular the custom of demining machines on the basis of domestic T-64A tanks.

The participants of the meeting discussed the possibility of involving the working group with the leading of the Viceremer-Minister of Ukraine.

The group should work out the general concept of work, consider the issue of unification of technology, licensing of production.

Regarding their own production, representatives of the Federation of Employers of Ukraine have asked that there are both staff and modern machines and other equipment in the country.

![](Images/AРМІЯINFORM/2023-04-07T41-00-00-04-00/e9a1a4cf-d169-4594-945f-00aca4e2eab9-1.jpg)After a roundtable voiced at the requirements and capabilities of the economy, the directors of the Tasks of domestic enterprises told about their opportunities to create technicians for transportation of explosive objects, in particular, the armored vehicles they already produce, as well as the means .

At the end of the event, Alexander Pavlyuk in a comment to the correspondent of the Armyinformis:

- Yes, many problematic issues are raised. But it was only the first, basic stage work. And we should attract our businesses as much as possible, because it is a raising of the economy and the prospect for Ukraine.

